\">phosphorus</span></li>\n        </ul>\n      </li>\n    </ul>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<hr><span id=\"purpleculture_examples\">①哀憐：憐憫。憐恤。可憐。同病相憐。<br>②愛：憐才(愛惜人才)。憐念。憐愛。愛憐。憐香惜玉(因香、玉可供玩賞，使人起憐愛之心，特指對女子的愛惜)。顧影自憐。<br><a href=\"https://www.purpleculture.net/dictionary-details?word=%E6%86%90%E6%86%AB\" class=\"sword\">憐憫</a> [ <a href=\"allsetlearning-lian2.mp3\" class=\"pinyin tone2\">lián</a> <a href=\"allsetlearning-min3.mp3\" class=\"pinyin tone3\">mǐn</a> ]: to take pity on; pity; mercy<br><a href=\"https://www.purpleculture.net/dictionary-details?word=%E6%86%90%E6%83%9C\" class=\"sword\">憐惜</a> [ <a href=\"allsetlearning-lian2.mp3\" class=\"pinyin tone2\">lián</a> <a href=\"allsetlearning-xi1.mp3\" class=\"pinyin tone1\">xī</a> ]: to take pity on; to feel tenderness toward<br><a href=\"https://www.purpleculture.net/dictionary-details?word=%E6%86%90%E6%84%9B\" class=\"sword\">憐愛</a> [ <a href=\"allsetlearning-lian2.mp3\" class=\"pinyin tone2\">lián</a> <a href=\"allsetlearning-ai4.mp3\" class=\"pinyin tone4\">ài</a> ]: to have tender affection for; to love tenderly; to pamper sb</span>\n<hr>\n<div>\n  <div>\n    <div><span class=\"tc\">(Simplified: 怜)</span></div><b>Chinese Definition:</b>\n    <div><b>Pictophonetic</b>: <span class=\"semantic\"><a class=\"dictips\">粦</a></span> indicates the sound; <span class=\"phonetic\"><a class=\"dictips\">忄</a></span> (heart) conveys the meaning.</div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div>HSK: 4</div>\n<hr><span><span style=\"color:#1ce63d\">Kanshudo mnemonic:</span>the rice you oppose (<a href=\"/kanji/%E7%B2%A6\">粦</a>) makes your heart (<a href=\"/kanji/%E5%BF%84\">忄</a>) take pity</span>\n<div><span style=\"color:tomato\">Chinese</span>: Your state of mind for children who aren't happy with the jack o lantern they made, is pity. &nbsp;</div>\n<hr>\n<div><span style=\"color:#f5950f\">Meaning:</span> pity<br><span style=\"color:#f5950f\">Hanzi:</span> 怜<br><span style=\"color:#f5950f\">Story:</span> A soldiers state of mind can change to pity even though he had strict orders to carry out the mission objective.<br><span style=\"color:#f5950f\">Kind:</span> traditional<br><img src=\"lf_24604.gif\"></div>\n<div>\n  <hr>\n</div>\n<hr><img src=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/kangxiArchaic.php?hash=e7e44773e4bb3f4c22780e6fee4105ab\"><br>\n<div class=\"two_children__horiz_even\">\n  <div id=\"humanum_full_description\">從「 心 」，「 粦 」聲，本義為哀憐、憐憫。《說文》：「哀也。从心，粦聲。」《商君書‧兵守》：「壯男壯女過老弱之軍，則老使壯悲，弱使彊憐。」 「 憐 」可表示喜愛、疼愛。《莊子‧秋水》：「夔憐蚿，蚿憐蛇，蛇憐風，風憐目，目憐心。」鍾泰發微：「憐，愛羡也。」</div>\n  <div id=\"humanum_full_description_en\">From the sound of \" heart\" and \" 粦\", the original meaning is pity and mercy. \"Shuowen\": \"Sorrow. From the heart, the sound.\" \"Shang Junshu·Bingshou\": \"Strong men and strong women pass the old and weak army, then the old makes the strong and the weak, the weak makes the strong pity.\" \" Pity\" can mean affection and affection. \"Zhuangzi·Qiu Shui\": \"Kui pity, pity the snake, the snake pity the wind, the wind pity the eyes, the eyes pity the heart.\" Zhong Tai tweeted, \"Pity, love envy.\"</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"hanziyuan\">\n  <div class=\"etymology-nav\" id=\"&#x6190;\">\n    <div class=\"alert alert-success etymology-alert m-0\" role=\"alert\"></div>\n    <div class=\"row bg-info border-purple border-top mx-0 row-eq-height\" id=\"E03641\">\n      <div class=\"col-md-3 col-sm-4 p-0\">\n        <div class=\"p-1\">\n          <p></p>\n          <p><b>Traditional in your browser 繁体字的浏览器显示:</b><span class=\"text-lg\">&#x6190;</span></p>\n          <p><b>Traditional in Unicode standard 繁体字的Unicode标准:</b><a href=\"https://www.unicode.org/cgi-bin/GetUnihanData.pl?codepoint=6190\" target=\"_blank\">U+6190</a><img src=\"https://www.unicode.org/cgi-bin/refglyph?24-6190\"></p>\n          <p><b>Older traditional characters 旧繁体字/异体字:</b> Not exist</p>\n          <p><b>Simplified in your browser 简体字的浏览器显示:</b><span class=\"text-lg\">&#x601C;</span></p>\n          <p><b>Simplified in Unicode standard 简体字